      "created_at": "2026-04-28T06:28:11Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-28T06:28:11Z",
      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "An idea to address this is for the p2p thread to be a bit more async, that is when a block B comes from peer X on the `msghand` thread, we pass that block to a separate `validation` thread  and pause peer X, while still continuing to do work for other peers. I think we could potentially extend that so that if peer Y sends a bip157 query related to pending block B, we also pause peer Y.",
